Episodes.Title: Rise and Shine
Episodes.Plot: A glimpse into the interior of SquidWard's Easter Island Head proves that his morning routine is nothing but shame.

Episodes.Title: Waiting
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob learns that his cereal box offers a free toy, so he camps out next to his mailbox to wait for his treasure to arrive.
Episodes.Writer: Nate Cash, Tuck Tucker, Steven Banks

Episodes.Title: Sing a Song of Patrick
Episodes.Plot: Patrick gets an offer to write a song, but he can't remember anything. When he wrote his first poem, he got hit by dodgeballs! It seems like Patrick had made a song, but it is horrible and they can't play it on the radio station. So Patrick puts the song up on the antenna, and it is so bad, it starts an angry mob!
Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Steven Banks

Episodes.Title: Born to be Wild
Episodes.Plot: A very bad motorcycle gang is coming to Bikini Bottom and SpongeBob tries to warn everyone, but at first, they won't listen. Then, everyone sees them coming and panic. Now what will they do?

Episodes.Title: Best Frenemies
Episodes.Plot: A new soft drink causes Mr. Krabs and Plankton to both worry about their restaurants, and they work together to find the secret of the soft drink.

Episodes.Title: Spy Buddies
Episodes.Plot: Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on Plankton.
Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Dani Michaeli

Episodes.Title: Boat Smarts
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob and Squidward star in an instructional boating video with Squidward as the good driver and SpongeBob as the bad driver.
Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Richard Pursel

Episodes.Title: Good Ol' Whatshisname
Episodes.Plot: Mr. Krabs pits SpongeBob against Squidward in a work contest, promising the winner a fabulous prize. The challenge is to find out all of the customers' names. When they cover almost all of them, Squidward tries desperately to find out the name of a grumpy man.
Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Richard Pursel

Episodes.Title: The Krusty Sponge
Episodes.Plot: After receiving a good review from a food critic, Mr. Krabs decides to sell SpongeBob merchandise. Including pens, aprons, coasters and even a Spongey Patty! However, the patties turn whoever eats them into a sponge zombie.

Episodes.Title: Squid Wood
Episodes.Plot: Squidward refuses to play with SpongeBob, so SpongeBob makes a ventriloquist dummy of Squidward. But everyone prefers the dummy over the real thing!
Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Chris Mitchell, Dani Michaeli

Episodes.Title: New Digs
Episodes.Plot: After he is late for work by one minute, SpongeBob is worried that it'll happen again, so he decides to move into the Krusty Krab. At first, Squidward completely enjoys the fact that SpongeBob's no longer living next to him, but Mr. Krabs is concerned when SpongeBob is taking up too much space in his office and, worse of all, scaring away his customers.
Episodes.Writer: Nate Cash, Tuck Tucker, Richard Pursel

Episodes.Title: Krabs Ã  la Mode
Episodes.Plot: Plankton freezes the Krusty Krab in an attempt to get rid of its customers. However, the restaurant still finds its success by turning into a popular ice skating and hockey rink.
Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Eric Shaw

Episodes.Title: To Love a Patty
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob falls in love with a Krabby Patty and blows off all of his friends and their activities
Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Eric Shaw

Episodes.Title: Breath of Fresh Squidward
Episodes.Plot: When Squidward finds out that SpongeBob and Patrick have been sneaking into his room every night to watch the sunrise, he installs an electrical fence to shield them away. But when he accidentally get zapped by his own fence, he turns into the happiest guy in town. Eventually, SpongeBob is tired of him when Squidward is stealing his job and his employee-of-the-month fame.
Episodes.Writer: Nate Cash, Tuck Tucker, Richard Pursel

Episodes.Title: Roller Cowards
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob and Patrick are excited because they are going to ride "The Fiery Fist O' Pain." But when SpongeBob has terrible experience in a nightmare, they are both too scared to ride it and stall by riding the kiddie rides first.
Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Steven Banks

Episodes.Title: Bucket Sweet Bucket
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob, Patrick, and Squidward are tricked into fixing up the Chum Bucket by Plankton. SpongeBob and Patrick are trying to make it pizzazzy by stealing pieces from the Krusty Krab and end up rebuilding the Krusty Krab instead.
Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Zeus Cervas, Richard Pursel

Episodes.Title: The Original Fry Cook
Episodes.Plot: SpongeBob tries to impress a world-renowned chef named Jim, who once worked at the Krusty Krab. He realizes Jim is much better than him, so SpongeBob writes Mr. Krabs a resignation letter because he is sure that he will be fired and replaced by him. Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Steven Banks, Dani Mich

Episodes.Title: Night Light
Episodes.Plot: After reading a story about the bogeyman, SpongeBob becomes scared of the dark, buying night lights in bulk. Patrick admits he is scared of the dark too. Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy come to the pineapple and say that there is nothing to be afraid of, after he flashes the Mermaid Man signal. But an enemy of Mermaid Man, known as The Moth, arrives. Episodes.Writer: Casey Alexander, Chris Mitchell, Steven Banks

Episodes.Title: Money Talks
Episodes.Plot: Mr. Krabs' money talks after an encounter with the Flying Dutchman.
Episodes.Writer: Luke Brookshier, Tom King, Dani Michaeli

Episodes.Title: Spongebob Vs. the Patty Gadget
Episodes.Plot: A machine replaces SpongeBob, so they have a contest to see who can make the most Krabby Patties.
